String Operations\
\
String: sequence of characters\
Can bind to another variable (Name = \'93Michael Jackson\'94)\
We can index elements in strings\
\
It is helpful to think of a string as a list or tuple\
We can treat the string as a sequence and perform sequence operations (such as indexing).\
\

\f1\b Stride value\

\f0\b0 Name[::2]: \'93McalJcsn\'94\
\

\f1\b Slicing\

\f0\b0 Name[0:5:2]: \'93Mca\'94 \

\f2\i The above operation takes every second value up to index 4\
\

\f0\i0 len(\'93Michael Jackson\'94) returns length of the string\
\

\f1\b You can concatenate strings using string addition\

\f0\b0 Name = \'93Michael Jackson\'94\
Statement = Name + \'93 is the best\'94\
Statement: \'93Michael Jackson is the best\'94\
\

\f1\b We can replicate values of a string using string multiplication\

\f0\b0 3*Name \'97> \'93Michael Jackson Michael Jackson Michael Jackson\'94\
\

\f1\b Escape sequences\

\f0\b0 \\ are meant to proceed escape sequences\
Escape sequences are strings that are difficult to input.\
\

\f1\b New line\

\f0\b0 print(\'93Michael Jackson \\n is the best\'94)\
Michael Jackson\
 Is the best\
\

\f1\b Tab\

\f0\b0 print(\'93Michael Jackson \\t is the best\'94)\
Michael Jackson	is the best\
\

\f1\b Backslash\

\f0\b0 print(\'93Michael Jackson \\\\ is the best\'94)\
Michael Jackson \\ is the best\
\
# r will tell python that string will be display as raw string\
print(r" Michael Jackson \\ is the best" )\
Michael Jackson \\ is the best\
\

