\f0\b0 Strings are sequences and have applied methods that work on lists or tuples.\
Strings also have methods that only work on strings.\
\
A = \'93Michael Jackson\'94\
A.upper() - makes elements of string upper case\
A.replace() - replaces first string input with second string input\
A.find() - finds substrings, returns first index of sequence\
